"\"use strict\";Object.defineProperty(exports,\"__esModule\",{value:true});Object.defineProperty(exports,\"default\",{enumerable:true,get:function(){return _default}});function _createMdxContent(props){var _components=Object.assign({h2:\"h2\",p:\"p\",blockquote:\"blockquote\",a:\"a\",strong:\"strong\",em:\"em\"},props.components);return Vue.h(Vue.Fragment,null,\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.h2,null,\"The Transparent Star\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"Loneliness is a terminal illness.\\nWhen it comes to the ultimate questions, humanity as a whole remains a poor student, standing awkwardly during an impromptu quiz, like a stranded fish opening and closing its mouth, yet unable to offer an answer of equal finality.\\nAnd yet, I have seen people who, through their own actions, tried again and again to call back companions standing at the edge of death.\\nThese answers may not be perfect, nor are they free from failure, but they are enough to make even death itself fall silent.\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"Miyako Kujo was one of them.\\nAs they once said, they were not a full moon, only a scattered star.\\nIn the vast digital world, they left little trace.\\nRarely eye-catching, rarely loud.\\nAnd yet we may never know how many people, standing at the cliff edge of their own lives, once caught sight of that faint, flickering star. And among them, how many were given, even just once, the chance to choose life again, because Miyako stayed with them.\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"As a companion active on international social platforms, Miyako understood their limits well.\\nThey knew that those they could reach were only a small number of people, those who had slipped past the silence imposed on certain topics within the Simplified Chinese internet, and found themselves on platforms like Twitter/X.\\nEven so, they never stopped extending gentle feelers toward the world.\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"They once wrote:\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.blockquote,null,\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"I hope to follow the example of a blogger I admire, to offer a few warm words to anyone surrounded by heavy feelings. If you come across this while scrolling, please @ me.\"),\"\\n\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"Perhaps Miyako did not expect replies.\\nNor was they seeking interaction.\\nThey was simply lighting up their own faint glow, which was quiet and steady.\\nThey let the world know that they were still here, still staying with us.\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"They rarely spoke of their own pressures or daily struggles.\\nInstead, they tried to hold others back from despair, to bless them when they reached for even the smallest hope again and again, wishing only that, in this cold world, they might hear an echo in response.\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"To someone who wrote, “I really want to be loved…”, they replied, “I love you.”\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"To the call, “It hurts so much… I’m so lonely… is anyone there?”, they answered, “I’m still here.”\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"Miyako was deeply empathetic.\\nNo matter how heavy the words carried by others, and no matter how often far beyond what one person could reasonably bear, they still chose to respond.\\nNot with empty comfort, but by truly placing their self in the other’s position.\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"In truth, even such limited conversations are already part of suicide intervention.\\nAnd yet, we also know that intervention does not always succeed.\\nAfter all, individual strength was limited, something Miyako had clearly thought about.\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"In the autumn of 2024, an article by \",Vue.h(_components.a,{href:\"https://twitter.com/HANLIANYI331\"},\"Han Lianyi\"),\" pointed out that the most crucial step in suicide intervention lies in analysing the crisis itself.\\nIn response, Miyako asked:\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.blockquote,null,\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"I see many expressions of suicidal thoughts on Twitter/X. I want to do something, but all I can access are their past posts.\\nEven private messages make deeper assessment difficult.\\nI can only rely on my own experience and words to help them calm down.\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"Is there a better way to offer comfort or specific ways of speaking that might make intervention more effective?\"),\"\\n\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"What few people noticed was that, even as Miyako reached outward with warmth and care, their own situation was far from easy.\\nTheir sorrow over loss came from a place they knew well—a darkness that had once nearly consumed them too.\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"They once said, “When I feel strong, I want to help those still stuck in the mud. Because I’ve been in the dark myself, I want others to face the light.”\\nAnd when others replied, “Stop trying to warm everyone else, you haven’t healed yourself,”\\nthey answered, “It’s only when I’m warming others that I truly feel I’m still alive.”\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"Even small things, such as helping two fellow passengers lift their luggage on a high-speed train could bring them quiet joy.\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.h2,null,\"Lengthen night and shorten day\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"There is a clarity in Miyako’s poetry, a lightness stripped of ornament.\\nWhen someone wrote, “May the autumn wind know my heart,” they continued, “so the dust may scatter, and the true self be seen.”\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"They never avoided acknowledging their own smallness or powerlessness.\\nBetween poetry and daily words, the sun, the moon, and the stars appear again and again, mirroring and contradicting one another.\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"There is regret at being too small to light the world, and yet comfort in becoming one star among many, bringing even the slightest joy to others.\\nAnd when someone truly crossed distance and emptiness to draw near their heart, Miyako never held back warmth or blessing—becoming a sun for them.\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"But we must remember:\\nIn effect, the brilliant sun they once gazed upon was, only an ordinary star on Orion’s arm.\\nAnd what blocks light and warmth has never been anything more than distance and the void itself.\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,Vue.h(_components.strong,null,\"Poem One:\")),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.blockquote,null,\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"There is only one moon, and only one sun.\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"I cannot be the moon in someone else’s night,\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"nor the sun that lights their whole life.\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"So let me be a star.\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"Even if I cannot light their face,\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"even if I cannot show them the way,\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"when they look up,\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"I am still one among countless stars.\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"The joy of that moment,\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"a small part of it is mine.\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"And that is enough.\"),\"\\n\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,Vue.h(_components.strong,null,\"Poem Two:\")),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.blockquote,null,\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"I am not the sun or the moon in someone else’s sky.\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"I am only a star, too far away.\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"My light and warmth cannot reach them.\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"But I am my own sun.\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"When you cross light-years to come to me,\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"I will offer you my purest warmth,\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"my kindness,\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"my truest passion,\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"and my blessing.\"),\"\\n\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.h2,null,\"Where the World Paused\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"Companionship is never without cost.\\nAs this long journey of staying with others drew toward its end, in May 2024, Miyako once left a comment beneath another user seeking death and asked whether they could share information about acquiring drug.\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"After that, they rarely spoke of their own life.\\nWe do not know whether there were friends nearby in those final days, what their family relationships were like, or whether they was struggling with mental illness.\\nPerhaps time had once wrapped their old wounds gently, but it could not heal those that continued to bleed unseen.\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"In the end, the words \",Vue.h(_components.em,null,\"“you haven’t healed yourself”\"),\" became prophecy.\\nThis companion, who had been soaked by the rain and wanted only to hold an umbrella for others, who tried in every way to bring light to those around them eventually left us.\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"Perhaps this was not truly their ending.\\nIt is only that, in this particular playthrough, the world stopped them at a single moment in time. We do not have the ability to \",Vue.h(\"ruby\",null,\"reload a save file\",Vue.h(\"rt\",null,\"OVERLOAD\")),\" and begin again.\\nAll that remains before us is this outcome.\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"Rabindranath Tagore, who like Miyako, loved the crescent moon and the star-filled sky once wrote:\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.blockquote,null,\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"On the seashore of endless worlds, children meet.\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"The infinite sky is motionless overhead and the restless water is boisterous.\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"On the seashore of endless worlds, the children meet with shouts and dances.\",Vue.h(\"sup\",null,Vue.h(\"a\",{href:\"#footnote-1\",id:\"footnote-ref-1\"},\"1\"))),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"Life is like a major sea through,  we meet with a narrow boat Lane.\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"When he died, we join the trip, and it has also learned a different world.\",Vue.h(\"sup\",null,Vue.h(\"a\",{href:\"#footnote-2\",id:\"footnote-ref-2\"},\"2\"))),\"\\n\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"To this day, we cannot know whether, at the moment Miyako took leave of a world they did not truly love.\\nYet still believed there was \",Vue.h(_components.a,{href:\"https://x.com/windward0032/status/1838489443411661269\"},\"“something here still worth loving”\"),\", they ever thought of those distant seas, violent or silent, where stars so often go unnoticed.\\nStars that once held the hands of countless children, and watched them safely home.\\nPerhaps the truth was never quite as Miyako once said “I could not even show someone the way.”\\nFor on moonless nights at sea, the stars are the only lighthouse there is.\\nThey may at times have felt far removed from this world, distant and estranged.\\nBut not once did they let their light go out.\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(_components.p,null,\"Miyako was no longer with us, if someone should ask why the sky seems to be missing something, you might tell them this:\\nperhaps Miyako was only afraid that, in another world, there are children who are still afraid of the dark, still at risk of losing their way, and they wanted to go and keep watch over another boat.\"),\"\\n\",Vue.h(\"ol\",null,Vue.h(\"li\",{id:\"footnote-1\"},\"from Gitanjali No. 60, Rabindranath Tagore\",Vue.h(\"a\",{href:\"#footnote-ref-1\"},Vue.h(\"svg\",{viewBox:\"0 0 16 16\",version:\"1.1\",id:\"svg1\",\"xmlns:xlink\":\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink\",xmlns:\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\",\"xmlns:svg\":\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\",style:\"margin-left: 0.5rem; margin-bottom: -2px; width: 1rem; height: 1rem\"},Vue.h(\"defs\",{id:\"defs1\"},Vue.h(\"linearGradient\",{id:\"linearGradient3\"},Vue.h(\"stop\",{style:\"stop-color